## Bind Lakebase by Postgres database name (drop ``lakebase_database_id``)

Context: Operators prefer the UI-visible Postgres database name
(``databricks_postgres``, etc.) over the opaque ``db-…`` resource
segment. The bundle now uses ``lakebase_postgres_database`` as the
final ``…/databases/<name>`` path segment only; ``lakebase_database_id``
was removed.

Changes:

1. databricks.yml
   Postgres binding ``database`` path uses ``${var.lakebase_postgres_database}``; comments note the rare fallback if a workspace only accepts ``db-…`` ids.
2. README.md
   Lakebase callout lists variables without ``lakebase_database_id``.
3. scripts/bootstrap-lakebase-perms.sh
   Comment references ``lakebase_postgres_database``.

