## Prefer Apps Volume binding over stale Lakebase registry triplet

Context: On Lakebase-backed Databricks Apps, ``RegistryCfg.from_domain``
preferred the ``registries`` Postgres row for catalog/schema/volume
before ``REGISTRY_VOLUME_PATH``. Rows often still held the static env
default ``OntoBricksRegistry`` from ``app.yaml`` while the bundle-bound
UC Volume had a different name, so binary paths and UI drifted from the
mounted resource. The APScheduler boot path also ignored
``REGISTRY_VOLUME_PATH`` and always used ``REGISTRY_*`` env defaults.

Changes:

1. src/back/objects/registry/RegistryService.py
   Parse bound ``REGISTRY_VOLUME_PATH`` first; when Lakebase returns a
   row, replace catalog/schema/volume with the binding when it parses.
2. src/back/objects/registry/scheduler.py
   ``_resolve_creds``: use parsed volume path for catalog/schema/volume
   when set (matches request-path resolution).
3. src/back/objects/session/DomainSession.py
   Docstring for ``delta`` updated to describe merged precedence.
4. tests/test_registry.py
   Renamed/adjusted Lakebase triplet test; added scheduler coverage for
   volume path override.
5. tests/test_domain_session.py
   ``delta`` test expects binding when path is injected under Lakebase.

Modified files:
- src/back/objects/registry/RegistryService.py
- src/back/objects/registry/scheduler.py
- src/back/objects/session/DomainSession.py
- tests/test_registry.py
- tests/test_domain_session.py

