## Default Lakebase Postgres database: ``ontobricks_registry``

Context: ``bootstrap-lakebase-perms.sh`` and docs assumed ``PGDATABASE``
``databricks_postgres`` while the sandbox Lakebase bind uses a dedicated
database ``ontobricks_registry``, so post-deploy grants looked in the
wrong DB and reported the registry schema missing.

Changes:

1. scripts/bootstrap-lakebase-perms.sh
   Default ``-d`` / ``DATABASE`` is ``ontobricks_registry``; comments
   document ``-d databricks_postgres`` for legacy layouts.
2. docs/deployment.md
   Step 5b and bundle variable prose aligned with the dedicated-DB layout.
3. databricks.yml
   Comment on ``list-databases`` example rows updated.
4. src/back/core/databricks/LakebaseAuth.py
   Docstring example lists both possible ``PGDATABASE`` values.
5. releases/ReleaseNotes_V0.2.0.md
   Bootstrap defaults bullet updated.

